  <titles>
    <title as="introduced" type="short">Long-Term Care and Retirement Security Act of 1999</title>
    <title as="introduced" type="official">To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to allow individuals a deduction for qualified long-term care insurance premiums and a credit for individuals with long-term care needs, to provide for an individual and employer educational campaign concerning long-term care insurance, and to amend title XIX of the Social Security Act to expand State long-term care partnerships by exempting 75 percent of partnership assets from Medicaid estate recovery.</title>
